result.execSummary:
The defendant Qualandra L Carr-Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Qualandra L Carr-Jones in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Defendant Qualandra L Carr-Jones in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNTS #1 and #2, dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT #3: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.  The Court finds that the State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS (CONCURRENT to any other sentence), in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served.  

COURT ORDERS:

- Defendant to pay the domestic violence surchage, DNA surcharge and victim/witness surcharge, by 5-14-2016, and if not paid a CIVIL JUDGMENT.
- Court waived the court fees (due to financial reasons).

Appeal rights given. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Copy given to defendant. 

48USC Section 922(g)(9) prohibits possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

  Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.  mld
